# SKOverlay.Position.bottomRaised

**Case**

Specifies that the overlay is at a raised position at the bottom of the screen.

## Declaration

```swift
case bottomRaised
```

## Discussion

Use this position in case your app uses a [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UIKit/UITabBar].

## Describing the Overlay’s Position

- **SKOverlay.Position.bottom**: Specifies that the overlay is at the bottom of the screen.
